oad-Spectrum SPF 46 (currently sold out across Canada)? Recommend specific, c=
urrently-purchasable products that are in stock and ship to / are stocked in =
Canada.

WHY THIS MATTERS / WHAT WE VALUE: We currently use and love EltaMD UV Clear S=
PF 46 (untinted) as a daily facial sunscreen. It is a mineral/physical sunscr=
een (zinc oxide, no chemical UV filters), fragrance-free, oil-free, non-comed=
ogenic, with added niacinamide + hyaluronic acid. We chose it because we beli=
eve it is good for health: it avoids chemical UV filters (oxybenzone, octinox=
ate, etc.) that carry hormone-disruption and reef-toxicity concerns, and it i=
s gentle on sensitive/acne-prone skin. We prefer organic/clean-ingredient pro=
ducts and are health-conscious about what we put on our skin daily. We are wi=
lling to spend more for cleaner ingredients/higher quality - price is not the=
 main constraint. Use case: daily facial wear, broad-spectrum, ideally SPF 40=
+ (SPF 30 minimum), cosmetically elegant enough to wear under makeup or a day=
 cream.

HARD CONSTRAINTS (a recommendation only counts if it meets ALL of these): (1)=
 Currently in stock from a reputable seller that ships to Canada (Vancouver, =
BC) - Canadian retailers preferred; US/international OK only if they reliably=
 ship here. Provide working product links and price (CAD where possible). (2)=
 Mineral/physical sunscreen - zinc oxide and/or titanium dioxide as the activ=
e filter. No oxybenzone, octinoxate, or other controversial chemical filters.=
 (3) Facial formulation (not a heavy body sunscreen). (4) Authentic/reputable=
 source - no grey-market or counterfeit risk.

WHAT TO WEIGH: Ingredient/health profile (certified-organic or clean ingredie=
nts, fragrance-free, EWG rating, third-party certifications like COSMOS/ECOCE=
RT organic or Made Safe, benzene-contamination track record, nano vs non-nano=
 zinc). How well it matches what we liked about EltaMD (gentle, non-comedogen=
ic, niacinamide/antioxidants, white-cast level - note tinted vs untinted). Ca=
nadian availability and ease of repurchase (consider Canadian-made organic br=
ands like Attitude, Green Beaver, plus retailers like Well.ca, Beautysense, W=
hole Foods, The Detox Market). Value at the premium tier. Be honest about gre=
enwashing - flag brands that market "natural/organic" without substantiation,=
 and acknowledge that a fully certified-organic sunscreen is chemically limit=
ed (the mineral active itself is not organic), so weigh "clean-leaning" reali=
stically rather than taking marketing at face value.

REQUIRED OUTPUT: A ranked shortlist (top 3-5) of specific products. For each:=
 product name + size + SPF, the active mineral filter, key clean/organic cred=
entials, where to buy in Canada (link + CAD price + in-stock status), how it =
compares to EltaMD UV Clear on health/ingredients and feel, and any caveats (=
white cast, availability, greenwashing). End with ONE overall top pick and a =
separate "best Canadian-made organic option" pick.

